section.section:
On a form approved by the Commissioner, the surplus lines broker shall:
make a clear and conspicuous written disclosure of:
any inspection fee;
the total amount of the policy fee;
the premium tax on the policy;
any financial interest in the person performing the inspection, if applicable; and
whether the surplus lines broker will receive compensation from the person that performs the inspection; and
notify the prospective insured of the option to obtain the inspection from another person who meets the requirements of or is approved by the surplus lines insurer.
